<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/545a.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">O’Brien</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-26"><hi rend="italic">January 26,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Bacon informs Mr. O’Brien that Austria-Hungary and Italy have been
                            invited to participate in International Opium Conference, and instructs
                            him to so inform the legations at Peking and Bankok.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>